Normalization


Save figure


Save figure
Save figure


Normalization method : each intensity is expressed relatively to a reference intensity, as a ratio of intensities. Intensities of the sample with the lowest number of missing values are used as reference intensities. Intensities are then centered by substracting the median of the ratios for each sample.
